Comment: 0,0:01:50.51,0:01:50.51,Default,,0,0,0,,SIGNS
Comment: 0,0:02:51.94,0:03:00.91,Title,,0,0,0,,Festival on the Night Before Gold-Hunting! \NFeelings for Vearth!
Comment: 0,0:23:31.56,0:23:35.52,Title,,0,0,0,,Enter God Eneru!! \NFarewell to the Survivors
Comment: 0,0:01:50.51,0:01:56.64,Sign,,0,0,0,,"Upper Yard" "Lovely Street" \N"Angel Beach"
Comment: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,OPENING
Comment: 0,0:21:54.50,0:21:54.50,Default,,0,0,0,,ENDING
Dialogue: 10,0:02:02.14,0:02:06.06,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't want to die, \Ngo back to the Blue Sea immediately!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:06.06,0:02:10.78,Default,,0,0,0,,If you've got any funny ideas about \Ndoing something on this island...
Dialogue: 10,0:02:11.28,0:02:14.70,Default,,0,0,0,,...we'll eliminate you along with Eneru!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:16.74,0:02:18.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Who're they?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:26.92,0:02:32.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So he fought this hard, even though \Nhe gave us this whistle for free...
Dialogue: 10,0:02:34.97,0:02:40.06,Default,,0,0,0,,As pirates, we can't back off when \Nthere's treasure close by, can we?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:40.06,0:02:44.60,Default,,0,0,0,,We've got enough enemies. \NIt's gonna be a survival game.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:48.19,0:02:51.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright! Let's do it! Gold hunting!!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:12.71,0:03:14.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Those beasts are problematic.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:14.85,0:03:17.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't we draw them away somehow?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:19.22,0:03:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright! I'll try!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:40.62,0:03:42.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Two... Three...
Dialogue: 10,0:04:01.97,0:04:02.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Laki!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:04.14,0:04:05.31,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:05.68,0:04:08.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Though I guess there's nothing you can do, \Nhanging there like that...
Dialogue: 10,0:04:10.81,0:04:13.82,Default,,0,0,0,,This is that important to you, huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:23.37,0:04:24.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Laki!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:29.25,0:04:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Run, Kamakiri!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:33.38,0:04:35.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I owe you one, Kamakiri...
Dialogue: 10,0:04:38.13,0:04:39.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Kamakiri!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:39.43,0:04:40.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Dammit!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:45.64,0:04:47.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Wyper! Kamakiri's been hurt!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:48.77,0:04:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:54.32,0:04:57.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Dammit! And we were so close!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:59.28,0:05:00.95,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you figure that?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:01.78,0:05:05.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Once night falls, we'll have \Nan even greater advantage.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:14.09,0:05:16.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Assist the wounded! \NWe're pulling back for now!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:17.05,0:05:18.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Meet back at the outer island!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:22.39,0:05:23.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I won't let you escape!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:23.94,0:05:25.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait, Ohm!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:26.97,0:05:28.06,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:29.60,0:05:31.64,Default,,0,0,0,,God Eneru wants to see us.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:43.99,0:05:44.87,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:46.49,0:05:49.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Those sounds seem to be getting farther away.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:49.63,0:05:54.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. The guerillas and priests are \Nprobably going home for the night.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:54.46,0:05:57.09,Default,,0,0,0,,We better hurry and get back, too.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:58.00,0:06:01.13,Default,,0,0,0,,– Wait for me, Zoro! \N– Hurry, or I'll leave you behind!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:01.13,0:06:03.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't know the way back!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:31.16,0:06:32.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Man, this is boring!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:32.66,0:06:34.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Who told you to stare at it?!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:35.46,0:06:39.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Your only job is to put the distilled \Nwater that collects in the container
Dialogue: 10,0:06:39.13,0:06:44.63,Default,,0,0,0,,into the canteens, so that we'll \Nhave drinking water for tomorrow!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:46.55,0:06:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Still...
Dialogue: 10,0:06:48.72,0:06:50.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Sanji! We got lots of things!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:50.97,0:06:53.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! Good work! What'd you find?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:53.48,0:06:55.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Walnuts, aloe, bananas, and garlic!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:55.77,0:06:56.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And rats and frogs.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:57.20,0:06:59.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Great! Toss it into the stew!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:59.32,0:07:02.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold it! \NThere were some weird ingredients just now!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:02.86,0:07:05.66,Default,,0,0,0,,You're right! How careless of me!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:05.66,0:07:07.20,Default,,0,0,0,,No garlic?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:07.20,0:07:08.91,Default,,0,0,0,,No! I wasn't talking about that!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:08.91,0:07:12.62,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong, Navigator?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:12.62,0:07:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow! Robin! What's that blue thing?! A gem?!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:17.12,0:07:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Pretty, isn't it? But no, it's not a gem.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:19.34,0:07:24.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, a salt crystal, huh? \NThat's a great find, Robin-{\i1}chan{\i0}!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:24.35,0:07:27.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I found it on the lakeshore. \NI thought it would be useful to have...
Dialogue: 10,0:07:27.97,0:07:32.47,Default,,0,0,0,,It sure would! \NSalt is vital to surviving in the wilderness!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:34.56,0:07:37.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll take half the garlic and aloe!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:37.23,0:07:41.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I can use it to make burn medicine \Nand antiseptic for the Sky Knight!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:41.23,0:07:41.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:42.44,0:07:44.57,Default,,0,0,0,,– What about the frogs? \N– No frogs.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:44.57,0:07:45.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Zoro!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:46.57,0:07:48.45,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not doing anything. Help out.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:51.33,0:07:55.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, my swords aren't \Nmeant to be used like this...
Dialogue: 10,0:07:55.70,0:07:59.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Quiet! \NDisobey the cook and you'll go without dinner!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:03.67,0:08:07.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?! We're eating rocks, too?! \NAre they any good?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:07.01,0:08:09.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Get real. This is stone stew.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:09.48,0:08:12.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The heat from the cooked stone boils the stew.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:12.18,0:08:13.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh...!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:13.39,0:08:17.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}Stew is great! \NYou get all the ingredients' nutrition without any waste!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:18.31,0:08:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I see!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:19.44,0:08:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! We're having stew...
Dialogue: 10,0:08:21.52,0:08:22.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't open it!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:24.40,0:08:27.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Sanji! I'm hungry!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:27.24,0:08:28.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not even cooked yet!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:29.32,0:08:33.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, didn't you just roast \Nand eat an entire skyshark?!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:33.37,0:08:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah... but that was just to tide me over.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:36.96,0:08:39.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Geez, what kind of stomach does he have?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:39.79,0:08:41.33,Default,,0,0,0,,How uneconomical...
Dialogue: 10,0:08:45.34,0:08:48.51,Default,,0,0,0,,What're you doing, Usopp? \NDinner's almost ready.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:48.51,0:08:54.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, just thought I'd start hauling \Nthe wood for the ship's repairs...
Dialogue: 10,0:08:54.60,0:08:57.43,Default,,0,0,0,,– You planning to swim across? \N– Huh? Yeah.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:57.43,0:08:59.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Those big sharks are in there.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:04.57,0:09:08.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I can fix it tomorrow! Let's get dinner, Zoro!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:10.24,0:09:11.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeesh...
Dialogue: 10,0:09:15.62,0:09:16.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright! Finished!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:17.32,0:09:19.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Ladies first. Got it?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:19.66,0:09:20.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:20.79,0:09:23.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright! Everyone in your seats!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:23.21,0:09:25.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll come around and serve it, \Nso eat before it gets cold!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:25.96,0:09:27.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, guys!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:27.17,0:09:30.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's begin our strategy meeting \Nto decide what to do tomorrow!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:30.63,0:09:33.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Ooh! Looks great!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:33.05,0:09:35.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Guys! T-Thanks.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:35.22,0:09:37.01,Default,,0,0,0,,We can do this while eating, so listen!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:37.43,0:09:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,– Right! \N– Right!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:40.60,0:09:43.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! Heart-shaped carrots!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:45.61,0:09:47.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You're really meticulous, Sanji!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:48.23,0:09:53.86,Default,,0,0,0,,How is it, huh?! Do you like my love stew?!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:53.86,0:09:55.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? What?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:56.28,0:09:57.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone ready?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:57.66,0:09:59.91,Default,,0,0,0,,First, let's review Noland's picture book!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:59.91,0:10:04.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It was 400 years ago when Noland \Nfirst discovered the city of gold.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:04.25,0:10:10.42,Default,,0,0,0,,But when he returned to Jaya years later, \Nthe gold ruins were gone!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:10.42,0:10:12.97,Default,,0,0,0,,This stew sure is good! Just like—
Dialogue: 10,0:10:14.18,0:10:16.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! Are you listening?!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:16.18,0:10:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, Nami-{\i1}san{\i0}! But he was...
Dialogue: 10,0:10:18.56,0:10:22.69,Default,,0,0,0,,These sky island boxed lunches are great, too!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:23.23,0:10:24.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Back to the story!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:24.98,0:10:29.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Basically, during those few years, \Nthis island, which is part of Jaya,
Dialogue: 10,0:10:29.23,0:10:30.53,Default,,0,0,0,,came up into the sky!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:31.61,0:10:34.49,Default,,0,0,0,,You mean it rode up the Knock-Up Stream?!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:34.83,0:10:37.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. That's the only possibility I can think of;
Dialogue: 10,0:10:37.37,0:10:41.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Cricket-{\i1}san{\i0} said the sea floor \Nexplodes at different places each time.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:41.70,0:10:45.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I could see an island flying \Nafter an explosion like that!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:46.21,0:10:52.38,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's hard to believe that forest \Non Jaya is the same as this one...
Dialogue: 10,0:10:52.38,0:10:56.68,Default,,0,0,0,,That's probably due to the \Ncomposition of sea and island clouds.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:57.43,0:10:59.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It appears the environment around this sky island
Dialogue: 10,0:10:59.51,0:11:02.93,Default,,0,0,0,,allows animals and plants to develop unusually quickly.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:02.93,0:11:07.86,Default,,0,0,0,,That also explains the civilization \Nthat was swallowed up by this forest.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:07.86,0:11:09.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So dejected...
Dialogue: 10,0:11:09.62,0:11:15.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Say, the South Birds that saved \Nus at the lake were {\i1}this{\i0} big!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:15.07,0:11:17.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, they probably got \Nbigger over those 400 years.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:17.95,0:11:19.53,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's strange...
Dialogue: 10,0:11:20.12,0:11:23.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Why did those huge South Birds save you?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:23.41,0:11:30.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I'm not really sure. \NBut they all called the Sky Knight "God"...
Dialogue: 10,0:11:31.59,0:11:35.38,Default,,0,0,0,,God?! Does that mean we \Nshould beat up this old man?!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:35.38,0:11:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course not, you stupid loudmouth!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:38.10,0:11:40.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, that's enough! Sit down, loudmouth!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:40.76,0:11:41.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah! Sit down!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:41.51,0:11:43.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Who's this "loudmouth"?!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:43.10,0:11:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It's you!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:44.06,0:11:49.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyways, remember what Noland's \Nlog said about the city of gold?!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:49.73,0:11:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I know! He saw gold!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:51.52,0:11:54.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Obviously, you loud loudmouth! \NQuit sayin' whatever comes to mind!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:54.86,0:12:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I recall there being a giant gold bell, \Nand that there were South Birds...
Dialogue: 10,0:12:00.87,0:12:04.66,Default,,0,0,0,,There was an incomprehensible \Nline on the last page of his log.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:04.66,0:12:07.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Just before he died, Noland wrote a passage
Dialogue: 10,0:12:08.08,0:12:10.63,Default,,0,0,0,,that said he saw gold in the "skull's right eye"...
Dialogue: 10,0:12:10.63,0:12:13.13,Default,,0,0,0,,That's it! Look at this!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:13.13,0:12:18.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I matched the size of Robin's Jaya map with the old Skypiea map!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:18.76,0:12:20.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just an approximation,
Dialogue: 10,0:12:20.43,0:12:24.31,Default,,0,0,0,,but when you put their locations \Nof the beach house together...
Dialogue: 10,0:12:25.64,0:12:28.81,Default,,0,0,0,,See! This is how Jaya looked 400 years ago!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:30.40,0:12:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,– Whoa! It's a skull! \N– It looks like a skull!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:35.03,0:12:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Well?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:35.78,0:12:37.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Awesome!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:37.07,0:12:38.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Way to go, Nami-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:38.70,0:12:40.57,Default,,0,0,0,,We did it!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:40.57,0:12:43.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, the "skull's right eye" is...
Dialogue: 10,0:12:45.16,0:12:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Right here!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:47.25,0:12:50.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Noland was referring to the \Nshape of the entire island.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:50.97,0:12:55.59,Default,,0,0,0,,But only half of it is left now, \Nso nobody could solve the mystery!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:56.38,0:12:59.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I see! So {\i1}that's{\i0} why...
Dialogue: 10,0:13:00.38,0:13:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Interesting...
Dialogue: 10,0:13:01.84,0:13:03.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Treasure!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:03.05,0:13:04.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Treasure!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:05.01,0:13:07.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So we just need to go straight to this spot!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:08.64,0:13:13.11,Default,,0,0,0,,We can't leave the boat, though, \Nso let's split into two teams tomorrow!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:14.48,0:13:16.28,Default,,0,0,0,,No doubt about it!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:16.28,0:13:19.74,Default,,0,0,0,,There's an enormous amount \Nof gold waiting for us here!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:43.55,0:13:44.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Wyper...
Dialogue: 10,0:13:44.39,0:13:47.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Genbou! How are Kamakiri's wounds?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:48.56,0:13:51.64,Default,,0,0,0,,They're tending to him over there right now.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:51.64,0:13:52.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Are they deep?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:53.23,0:13:54.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:54.19,0:13:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It's hard to believe he would be beaten...!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:57.36,0:14:00.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Ohm really is formidable...
Dialogue: 10,0:14:00.24,0:14:01.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I-I'm sorry...
Dialogue: 10,0:14:05.66,0:14:06.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It's...
Dialogue: 10,0:14:07.66,0:14:09.29,Default,,0,0,0,,It's my fault!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:18.92,0:14:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,What a meal!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:21.63,0:14:24.22,Default,,0,0,0,,– We get gold tomorrow! \N– That's right!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:25.18,0:14:27.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you think tomorrow'll be sunny, too?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:27.39,0:14:29.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we {\i1}are{\i0} above the clouds...
Dialogue: 10,0:14:29.43,0:14:33.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It's gotten pretty late. \NWe need to put out any unnecessary fires.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:33.60,0:14:35.94,Default,,0,0,0,,They'll only reveal our location to the enemy...
Dialogue: 10,0:14:37.06,0:14:42.78,Default,,0,0,0,,How foolish! Did you hear that, Usopp?! \NShe wants to put out the fire!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:43.65,0:14:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not her fault. \NShe's lived in darkness until now.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:50.16,0:14:51.08,Default,,0,0,0,,She just doesn't know.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:52.79,0:14:54.21,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:55.46,0:14:59.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You're {\i1}always{\i0} supposed to have a campfire!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:59.17,0:15:02.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The desire to have a campfire \Nwhen camping at night,
Dialogue: 10,0:15:02.30,0:15:05.18,Default,,0,0,0,,even if you're on your last legs, \Nis what makes one human!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:05.18,0:15:07.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}You're{\i0} the stupid ones!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:07.81,0:15:14.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Will you cut the crap already?! \NYou know how dangerous this forest is!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:14.39,0:15:14.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Do not!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:14.98,0:15:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,There are priests! There are guerrillas!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:17.44,0:15:21.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And even without them, \Nforests at night are dangerous anyways!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:21.78,0:15:24.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Who knows? There could be wild \Nanimals or monsters out there!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:24.53,0:15:25.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Monsters?!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:25.90,0:15:27.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Sky islands are scary, sky islands are scary...
Dialogue: 10,0:15:27.95,0:15:29.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Luffy!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:30.33,0:15:32.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this wood pile good enough?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:32.45,0:15:34.66,Default,,0,0,0,,You guys are serious about this, too?!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:35.75,0:15:40.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all right, Nami-{\i1}san{\i0}. \NWild animals are actually afraid of fires.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:40.75,0:15:44.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Behind you! \NThere's already something behind you!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:51.72,0:15:54.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! It's saying something! C'mere, Chopper!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:54.89,0:15:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:57.27,0:16:02.44,Default,,0,0,0,,"You outsiders are being too damn loud! \NGet to bed, you dumbasses!"
Dialogue: 10,0:16:02.86,0:16:04.28,Default,,0,0,0,,– Say what?! \N– Say what?!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:04.28,0:16:06.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not the one saying it!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:06.78,0:16:11.53,Default,,0,0,0,,"Don't tell me you bastards are \Nthinkin' about trashin' our turf!"
Dialogue: 10,0:16:11.91,0:16:14.66,Default,,0,0,0,,No, we were brought here against our will!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:15.12,0:16:19.54,Default,,0,0,0,,"This is {\i1}our{\i0} land! \NWho said you jerks could cook here?!"
Dialogue: 10,0:16:19.92,0:16:21.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh... Sorry!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:21.59,0:16:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,"This forest is ours! \NThe trees, the grass, everything!"
Dialogue: 10,0:16:29.47,0:16:32.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I won't let you have our treasure!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:34.56,0:16:38.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, look! Things seem even worse now! \NWhat do we do?!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:38.77,0:16:39.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Do something!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:39.85,0:16:40.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Me?!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:43.69,0:16:48.57,Default,,0,0,0,,"Forget it, guys. You ain't no match for them, even as a pack..."
Dialogue: 10,0:16:49.66,0:16:54.87,Default,,0,0,0,,"Girlie! You pack a mean punch! I like ya!"
Dialogue: 10,0:16:57.91,0:17:00.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Did we just work things out?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:00.21,0:17:00.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Seems that way.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:01.42,0:17:04.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Then let's all have a campfire together!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:04.59,0:17:06.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:13.01,0:17:16.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's get this party goin'! \NIt's the night festival before gold-hunting!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:20.77,0:17:22.73,Default,,0,0,0,,What is this?! It's delicious!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:23.15,0:17:26.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you guys make this juice? \NIt's delicious! More, please!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:33.20,0:17:34.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Yay!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:40.87,0:17:42.29,Default,,0,0,0,,What is this?! It's delicious!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:42.29,0:17:44.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's get the treasure!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:44.29,0:17:46.21,Default,,0,0,0,,– Gold! \N– Gold!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:50.72,0:17:53.51,Default,,0,0,0,,They even tamed the cloud wolves...
Dialogue: 10,0:17:55.18,0:18:00.39,Default,,0,0,0,,No one else living on Eneru's land \Nwould have such a wild party...
Dialogue: 10,0:18:00.39,0:18:02.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, you're awake! \NShould you be moving about?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:02.69,0:18:06.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I apologize for trying to help \Nbut causing trouble instead...
Dialogue: 10,0:18:06.11,0:18:08.53,Default,,0,0,0,,What're you talking about? You helped a lot!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:08.53,0:18:12.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks! I hear you saved Chopper and our ship.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:12.70,0:18:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It was nothing...
Dialogue: 10,0:18:13.78,0:18:15.95,Default,,0,0,0,,There's still some stew. Would you like some?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:15.95,0:18:19.37,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no. I thank you, but I'm \Nafraid I can't right now.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:21.25,0:18:24.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! You're up, weird old man! \NThanks for your help!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:24.83,0:18:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,– Let's dance! \N– Let's dance, Sky Knight!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:27.67,0:18:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You're supposed to be a doctor!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:30.88,0:18:33.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Old man! How is Conis-{\i1}chan{\i0}? Is she all right?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:34.27,0:18:38.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. \NShe and her father are at my house. Fear not.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:38.68,0:18:41.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Really?! That's great! I was so worried!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:41.93,0:18:44.94,Default,,0,0,0,,That's great! They're both safe!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:44.94,0:18:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright! Let's all toss Chopper into the air!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:47.44,0:18:48.11,Default,,0,0,0,,What for?!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:03.46,0:19:06.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard you talking earlier...
Dialogue: 10,0:19:07.00,0:19:10.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So this island was originally known as Jaya?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:10.13,0:19:11.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:11.13,0:19:18.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I take it you don't know why this \Nplace is now known as holy ground?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:25.94,0:19:28.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It's stuff like this that \Ncauses distractions in battle!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:28.94,0:19:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you here to get in our way, Laki?!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:33.32,0:19:36.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel truly sorry for Kamakiri...
Dialogue: 10,0:19:37.45,0:19:38.87,Default,,0,0,0,,We're up against priests!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:38.87,0:19:41.83,Default,,0,0,0,,If we lack any strength in battle, \Nwe'll never make it to God's Shrine!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:41.83,0:19:44.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I know apologizing won't fix everything!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:44.25,0:19:47.83,Default,,0,0,0,,But give that back! It's Aisa's treasure!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:47.83,0:19:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I promised I would get some Vearth for her!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:51.92,0:19:52.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:52.34,0:19:54.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Forgive me! Don't throw it away!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:57.51,0:20:00.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Kamakiri... Your wounds...
Dialogue: 10,0:20:01.30,0:20:03.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I can still fight.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:06.10,0:20:09.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You're right... now is the time \Nto take down Upper Yard.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:13.65,0:20:18.11,Default,,0,0,0,,With Satori gone, we put up a \Ngood fight during today's battle...
Dialogue: 10,0:20:18.61,0:20:22.33,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's attack again tomorrow, Wyper...
Dialogue: 10,0:20:29.79,0:20:36.67,Default,,0,0,0,,For you Blue Sea people, the ground \Nhere must seem quite natural.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:36.67,0:20:37.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:38.84,0:20:40.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:41.39,0:20:46.22,Default,,0,0,0,,But this is something that does \Nnot normally exist in the sky.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:46.77,0:20:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Island cloud does raise plant life, \Nbut it does not give birth to it.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:51.94,0:20:55.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Neither greenery nor soil is \Nnaturally found in the sky...
Dialogue: 10,0:21:02.53,0:21:06.12,Default,,0,0,0,,We call this "Vearth."
Dialogue: 10,0:21:07.87,0:21:13.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It is the very object of eternal \Nadmiration for those living in the sky.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:16.30,0:21:21.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Once we defeat Eneru, we won't need \Nto revere a single bag of Vearth.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:23.18,0:21:25.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, Wyper?
Dialogue: 10,0:21:29.64,0:21:33.98,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going back. \NTo the 400-year-old homeland of the Shandians!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:10.79,0:23:12.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Gold-hunting, at last!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:12.66,0:23:15.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I, Usopp-{\i1}sama{\i0}, am president of \Nthe Lowering-the-Merry Company!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:15.87,0:23:18.04,Default,,0,0,0,,– Hold on, President! \N– President!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:18.42,0:23:21.25,Default,,0,0,0,,– There is nothing I can't do! \N– Just get working, President.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:21.25,0:23:24.97,Default,,0,0,0,,But now you're complete enemies of Eneru...
Dialogue: 10,0:23:25.38,0:23:26.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Next time, on One Piece:
Dialogue: 10,0:23:26.84,0:23:29.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Enter God Eneru!! \NFarewell to the Survivors
Dialogue: 10,0:23:30.10,0:23:32.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm gonna be the Pirate King!!
